-- Fitch raises Madrid, Barcelona ratings to 'BBB+' from 'BBB'
-- By Abinaya Vijayaraghavan
-- Fri May 02, 2014 12:19PM EDT
-- None



May 2 (Reuters) - Fitch Ratings raised the long-term foreign and local currency issuer default ratings of Spain's Madrid and Barcelona to "BBB+" from "BBB."

Fitch said the ratings of Barcelona reflected the city's strong budgetary performance and debt metrics.  Madrid's ratings reflected its enhanced budgetary performance and debt stabilization, Fitch said in a statement. (http://r.reuters.com/han98v)